Key Match Events: Ben Stokes scored 108 runs for England
The Netherlands was all out for 179, chasing 340 for victory
Adil Rashid claimed 3-54, Moeen Ali bagged 3-42, and David Willey took 2-19 for England
Post-Match Reflections: Ben Stokes expressed pleasure about the team's win and getting back on winning terms
Miscellaneous Highlights: England ended their five-match losing streak at the men's Cricket World Cup
Others: The win lifted England off the bottom to seventh in the 10-team standings with four points, above Bangladesh, Sri Lanka and the Dutch on net run rate
The Dutch dropped to 10th place but is still in the hunt for a Champions Trophy spot and face unbeaten India next in Bengaluru
